column5: Had a couple hours late this afternoon and tried a completely new spot today for my second time out this year and was pleasantly surprised.  First one broke me off, next one was a grandma hookset, lol, next one I landed and then a 10lb+ Brute broke me off just before I left.  Was a fun couple hours nonetheless.  Warm enough to get a few Jumps out of her  Even though she took me a couple minutes to get her in and 10 seconds for the pic,...she took almost no revival, took off like a bullet!!!  Lets let the wild ones swim
Beauty! Hope i can do the same tomarrow, nothin like the the first few steelies of the year!
hey nice lookin bow    i love this time of year for trout.  if you dont mind me askin were are sum good rivers  that you open this time of year
Nice!  Hoping to get out myself tomorrow afternoon.  Taking the kids for crappies in the morning.
That's pretty awesome StoneFly Good to see you back at it Thanks for sharing Leechman
